The Federal Government has stated that it would continue to pay attention to the underserved in Nigeria’s rural areas. Goddy Jedy-Agba, the Minister of State, Power, who said this when he inaugurated the Rural Electrification Agency (REA) board, promised that the Federal Government would accomplish the target of 30 per cent renewables of 30 gigawatts of electricity by 3030. He tasked the new board members to light up the hinterlands, adding that although a part-time board, the federal government expected them to give their best to ensure that the agency meets all Key Performance Indices (KPIs). Old Transmission Substations Goes Digital As TCN Takes Delivery… KEDCO Cautions New Tenants On Outstanding Bills He said from time to time, the indices would be reviewed for regular adjustment to meet with the government’s aspirations in the sector, urging the new inductees to minimise friction among themselves. Abdulazeez Musa-Yar’Adua is the board’s Chairman and Managing Director/CEO of the organisation.Mr. Ahmad Salihijo, is a member. Other members of the board representing the six – geopolitical zones include, Michael Oluwagbemi (representing the South West), Chidi Nwogu (representing the South-east) and Catherine Ajibike (representing the South-south). In addition, Dr Abdullahi Garba represents the North-west on the board, Dr. Abdul Umar, the North-east, while Mohammed Badamasuiy represents the North-central.